[[WP:AES|←]]Created page with 'Dear Pagemanager91,  Please stop deleting the info on the Burnley F.C. Wikipedia page. It is very childish, as is my username and when I deleted the info on the...'
Brought the introduction back, as this was deleted for no reason.

Edited bugs: Wolves are the most successful town team (13 honours won before 2000 when Wolverhampton turned from a town into a city). Also, Wanderers F.C. have also won the FA Cup three times in a row.

Most of the "facts" are untrue. E.g. Wolves are the most successful town team in England (13 trophies won before 2000 when Wolverhampton turned from a town into a city). Also, the added "info" was not objectively formed and it was wrongly paraphrased.

Intro: most of the stated "facts" are wrong. E.g. Blackburn aren't the most successful town team, Wolves are (they have won 13 trophies before 2000 when Wolverhampton turned from a town into a city). Also, the introduction wasn't objectively formed.

1. The population of approx. 87,000 is the population of the WHOLE Borough of Burnley, thus including towns like Padiham. The real population will probably be around 75,000, but this can not be clarified (yet), so we should be keeping hold on the data...
